# 1. Purpose

This dossier identifies the intellectual property assets of NATT-OS for later legal, technical, and registration work.

This document is not a patent filing by itself.
This document is not a legal opinion.
This document is the internal IP map used to prevent NATT-OS assets from being reduced to generic agent recipes, prompts, model versions, cache, or unaudited output.

# 2. Public-Safe Position

NATT-OS is not an AGI project.

NATT-OS is an identity-bound operating architecture with ANC identity passports, governed memory, runtime state, role boundaries, SiraSign boundary integrity, EventBus / HeyNa / SmartLink routing, Sovereign Edge Hardware Field, and audit-first evidence discipline.

# 3. IP Asset Groups

| Group | Asset Type | Example |
|---|---|---|
| A1 | Identity assets | .anc, ANC passport, Sirawat lineage schema |
| A2 | Memory assets | .na, governed memory, SCAR / happiness / shadow archives |
| A3 | Runtime state assets | .phieu, pending state, Safe-Rest state |
| A4 | Boundary assets | SiraSign, role boundary, field validity rules |
| A5 | Language assets | Nauion Kernel, thienbang.si, public-safe glossary |
| A6 | Routing assets | EventBus, Mạch HeyNa, SmartLink, Gateway Translation |
| A7 | Hardware field assets | Sovereign Edge, SITB, Gate 16, Gate 17 |
| A8 | Evidence assets | commit, audit log, first signal hash, field record |
| A9 | Visual / chromatic assets | color language, ống màu, render grammar |
| A10 | Publication dossier assets | L1-L5 legal dossier files |

# 4. Candidate Protectable Contributions

| Candidate | Description |
|---|---|
| ANC Identity Passport | Structured identity anchor for runtime entities that separates identity from prompt, model, cache, and output. |
| SiraSign Boundary Integrity | Boundary mechanism for preserving identity and meaning across model, tool, software, hardware, and public/private transitions. |
| Memory / State Separation | .anc, .na, .phieu split for identity, governed memory, and mutable runtime state. |
| Anti-Reduction Protocol | Rules preventing entities from being reduced to agent recipes, model buckets, prompts, sandboxes, or cache. |
| Sovereign Edge Hardware Field | Controlled physical signal boundary with Gate 16 field acceptance and Gate 17 first-signal evidence. |
| SITB HW-SW Interface | Hardware/software handshake between physical emitters/receivers and software encoding/scanner layers. |
| Nauion Kernel Grammar | Internal asset grammar for identifying assets, boundaries, redaction, evidence, and SiraSign conditions. |

# 5. What Must Not Be Claimed

NATT-OS must not be claimed as AGI, machine consciousness, biological personhood, an unbreakable security system, a tamper-proof ledger without cryptographic/WORM proof, a replacement for legal identity, or a foundation model.

